olive oil
1 tomato
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 avocado
1 tin sweetcorn
2 packet chicken breast
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
¼ cup water
1 packet BBQ sauce
drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet sour cream

• Finely chop tomato and baby leaves. Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and finely chop. Drain sweetcorn.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.

Little cooks: Help prep the avo!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook chicken and corn, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Reduce heat to medium-high, then add All-American spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the water and BBQ sauce and cook until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.

Little cooks: Take charge by adding the spice blend and sauces.

• In a medium bowl, add tomato, avocado, baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper and toss to combine. Set aside.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.
Little cooks: Take the lead by tossing the salsa!

• Build tacos by filling with BBQ chicken bites and corn and avocado salsa.
• Serve with a dollop of sour cream. Enjoy!